OL,7,FIn his written evidence, he said that
OL,8,Fit was "inconceivable" that anyone at
OL,9,Fthe Daily Mail would have carried out
OL,10,Fthe alleged activities.
OL,12,FMr Dacre also said: "The claims of
OL,13,Fcriminality made on behalf of Baroness
OL,14,FDoreen Lawrence in relation to the
OL,15,FDaily Mail's 15-year campaign for her
OL,16,Fmurdered son Stephen are especially
OL,17,Fbewildering and bitterly wounding to
OL,18,Fme personally.
