OL,7,FLater in his written evidence, Mr
OL,8,FDacre said that the "grave and
OL,9,Fsometimes preposterous allegations"
OL,10,Fmade in the case "have astonished,
OL,11,Fappalled and ` in the small hours of
OL,12,Fthe night ` reduced me to rage".
OL,14,FMr Dacre later said the claims had had
OL,15,Fa "deeply upsetting" and sometimes
OL,16,F"traumatic" impact on staff at the
OL,17,Fpaper, adding: "I have witnessed the
OL,18,Fanguish of honest, dedicated
OL,19,Fjournalists who, for three years now,
OL,20,Fhave had an insidious dark shadow
OL,21,Fhanging over their lives."
